                android:text="The Amber Fort, also known as the Amer Fort ranks in the popular tourist attractions in Jaipur. This magnificent fort is a great relic of the medieval Rajput style of construction. Initially, the fort was started by Raja Man Singh I of the Kachhwaja dynasty in the year 1592 and was completed by Raja Jai Singh at a later date. The final construction was done by Sawai Jai Singh. It took around two centuries for the whole Amber Fort to be built.The Amber Fort, Jaipur was built with white marble and red sandstone which makes it a spectacular sight. The attraction is increased by the Maotha Lake, which is located in the front of the fort. The fort's mirrors reflect the waters of the lake and create a great sight. "
